Remove the @Filo Pastry Sheets{1/2} from the fridge and bring it to room temperature, remove
from the packet and lay flat on the counter covered with a damp #tea towel{}. Preheat your
oven to 180°C. Trim the root from the @Leek{1}, halve lengthways and thinly slice. Chop the
@Potatoes{450%g} into 2cm chunks (no need to peel). Peel and grate the @Garlic Clove{1} (or
use a #garlic press{}). Fill and boil your #kettle{}.

Heat a drizzle of @Olive Oil{1%tbsp} in a large #saucepan{} on medium-high heat. Once the
oil is hot, add the leek, season with @salt{} and @pepper{} and fry until softened,
~{5-6%minutes}. Add the garlic to the pan, stir and cook for ~{1%minute}, then add the
potatoes, @Water{300%ml} and @Vegetable Stock Powder{1}.

Stir everything together and bring to the boil. Reduce the heat to medium, cover the pan
with a #lid{} or #tin foil{} and simmer until the potatoes are tender, ~{15-20%minutes}.
Stir every few minutes to ensure the mixture isn't sticking to the bottom of the pan.

> TIP: Add a splash of water if the mixture becomes too thick or the potatoes haven't
> yet softened.

While the potatoes simmer away, grate the @Mature Cheddar Cheese{60%g}. Once the potatoes
are cooked, stir the @Chopped Kale{100%g} into the mixture a handful at a time, cover
with a lid again and simmer until wilted, ~{3-4%minutes}. Stir in the
@Soured Cream{150%g} and Cheddar, bring to a boil, then remove from the heat. Taste and
add salt and pepper if you feel it needs it. Pour the mixture into a #baking dish{}.

Halve the filo pastry sheets to make squares. Scrunch each filo pastry sheet into a very
loose ball and place on top of the pie. Repeat until the whole pie is covered, making
sure not to overcrowd the pastry. Drizzle the whole thing with oil and then bake on the
top shelf of your #oven{} until the filo is golden, ~{10-15%minutes}.

Meanwhile, put the @Wholegrain Mustard{1%tbsp}, @Honey{15%g} and @Olive Oil{1%tbsp} into
a large #bowl{}. Season with salt and pepper and mix to combine. Trim the root from the
@Baby Gem Lettuce{1} and separate the leaves. Once the pie is cooked, add the baby gem
leaves to the dressing and toss to coat. Serve the pie on plates with the salad
alongside. Enjoy!